                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.2325/15c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Collier</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="31" xml:id="d408fn31">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, on the same date to the Ambassador in Peru, as telegram
                        No. 57.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-13T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1928—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. Please present my compliments to the President and Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs and express to them the gratification I feel. I am sure their action
                    will be for the best interest of Chile and be considered by all the world as a
                    high-minded and honorable step.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
